INSERT INTO "articles" VALUES(32,'Fiscal Sponsorship Basics','As part of Core Curriculum, Dianne will meet with new employees and discuss the following:<br><br><ol><li>Definition of F.S.<ul><li>Our definition Fiscal Sponsorship is a fundraising tool that enables artists and arts organizations to use some of the benefits of Fractured Atlas''s non-profit status to fundraise. This means they can get access to tax deductible donations and grants that are typically only available to nonprofit 501(c)(3) organizations.</li><li>Different models There are many models of fiscal sponsorship. Fractured Atlas operates what is referred to as a Model C or grantor-grantee relationship. Each project has a grant agreement with Fractured Atlas.</li><li>History of F.S. (external &amp; internal)</li><li>Why it exists</li><li>Our business model</li><li>Legal &amp; IRS overview - oversight</li><li>Theory of change</li><li>National Network of Fiscal Sponsors</li></ul></li><li>Who uses the program<ul><li>Examples of two projects</li><li>Where they come from</li><li>How they find us</li><li>How they use the program (temp vs ongoing)</li></ul></li><li>The application process<ul><li>Online app</li><li>Eligibility (tax ID, criteria, membership, U.S. address)</li><li>Staff and board review process</li></ul></li><li>How it works<ul><li>Contract and program manual</li><li>Text reviews</li><li>Donations and grants</li><li>Fund releases</li><li>Annual reports</li><li>Guidance/education</li><li>Admin fees</li></ul></li><li>More resources<ul><li>Program manual and contract</li><li>Webinars</li><li>KB</li><li>Reading: 6 Ways to Do It Right</li></ul></li><li>Member access<ul><li>Login access to dummy account</li></ul></li><li>Future of the program<ul><li>Microphilanthropy - why, when, how</li><li>Board presentation</li></ul></li></ol>','Deborah Kwon','2016-02-17 02:18:56.055753','2016-02-19 01:11:03.959075',9,'f');
INSERT INTO "articles" VALUES(33,'Insurance Basics','As part of Core Curriculum, Scott will meet with all new employees to discuss the following:<br><br><ol><li>History/Evolution of the FA Insurance Program</li><li>The Health Insurance program legacy<ul><li>why we got in</li><li>why we got out</li></ul></li><li>The structure of our program<ul><li>MDP</li><li>insurance companies</li><li>why use FA?</li></ul></li><li>What is insurance?<ul><li>general concepts</li><li>Why artists choose to purchase insurance</li><li>Insurance as financial security</li><li>types of insurance we sell</li><li>Commercial Lines</li><li>types of insurance we donâ€™t sell</li><li>Personal Lines</li><li>Health Insurance</li><li>Personal Car Insurance</li></ul></li><li>Member experience<ul><li>Map the member experience</li><li>application</li><li>staff communication</li><li>purchase</li><li>certificates</li><li>claims</li><li>endorsements</li><li>renewal</li><li>Our customer service philosophy</li></ul></li></ol>','Deborah Kwon','2016-02-17 02:24:45.043561','2016-02-17 02:26:32.292488',10,NULL);
INSERT INTO "articles" VALUES(34,'Artful.ly Basics','As part of Core Curriculum Training, Selena will meet with new employees to cover the following points:<br><br><ol><li>What is it?</li><li>Who is it for?</li><li>Two example orgs</li><li>Where is it?</li><li>Why track fans?</li><li>How can producers sell tickets?</li><li>How can producers take donations?<ul><li>For 501(c)(3)s</li><li>For fiscally sponsored projects</li></ul></li><li>How can producers sell memberships and passes?</li><li>Pricing</li><li>How is money sent to producers and where does it go?</li><li>Made Artful.ly<ul><li>Continual Development</li><li>Community Driven Design</li><li>Customer Support Resources</li></ul></li><li>Some Program History<ul><li>Timeline</li><li>Business Model</li><li>Key Funders</li><li>Roadmap Highlights</li></ul></li><li>The Artful.ly Team</li><li>Continued Learning Resources<ul><li>Cheat Sheet</li><li>Watch video <a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" href="http://www.artful.ly/about">www.artful.ly/about</a></li><li>Browse Artful.ly Knowledge Base</li></ul></li><li>Play with Demo Account<ul><li>List of tasks to do in Demo account</li><li>Appointment to review Demo tasks with Alessandra or Marcus</li></ul></li></ol>','Deborah Kwon','2016-02-17 02:29:06.710019','2016-02-17 02:29:06.710019',8,NULL);
