INSERT INTO "articles" VALUES(37,'Membership Overview','<div>**Types of Membership**</div><div><br></div><div>There are three different types of memberships: Community, Professional, and Organization.</div><div><br></div><div>The free Community level of membership provides access to benefits like free insurance quotes, the member calendar, SpaceFinder, Artful.ly, and special offers/discounts. SpaceFinder helps artists and arts organization find spaces in their neighborhood to either hold events, rehearse, and so on. Artful.ly offers artists a way to sell tickets and manage/communicate with their donors.</div><div><br></div><div>Professional membership has all the benefits at the Community level plus access to our full insurance program and access to apply for our fiscal sponsorship program. Since we are such a large&nbsp;</div><div>member organization, we are able to offer our member good rates on insurance policies. Our fiscal&nbsp;</div><div>sponsorship program helps artists fundraise for their works by incentivizing individual donations, obtain nonprofit rates, and more.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Organization membership provides all the benefits at the Professional level for up to three authorized users.</div><div><br></div><div>**Why do we have memberships?**</div><div><br></div><div>We have different memberships for the varying needs of the artist community. The membership dues is revenue generated by Fractured Atlas that goes towards sustaining the programs and services that we offer. The dues goes toward paying support staff, general administrative costs, software maintenance, and development.</div><div><br></div><div>**How many members do we have?**</div><div><br></div><div>We currently have about 50,000 members. There are live stats posted on our website (<a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" href="http://www.fracturedatlas.org/site/about/membership">www.fracturedatlas.org/site/about/membership</a>), but a more specific breakdown can be found under the Membership tab &gt; Membership Stats.</div><div><br></div><div>**How much money do we make from membership dues and how is that revenue used in our org?**</div><div><br></div><div><br></div>','Deborah Kwon','2016-02-19 15:33:10.747845','2016-02-19 15:33:10.747845',12,'t');
INSERT INTO "articles" VALUES(38,'Our Playbook','<span><b>Embrace Challenge.&nbsp;</b><br>We seek out challenging problems and relish opportunities to venture into unexplored territory. We are entrepreneurial and comfortable with high-risk, high-impact efforts. #EmbraceChallenge<br></span><span><br><b>Make It Happen.&nbsp;</b><br>We are agile, creative problem solvers with a pragmatic focus on concrete results. We do what needs to be done and do it well every day. #MakeItHappen<br></span><span><br><b>Seek Continuous Improvement.</b>&nbsp;<br>We are curious, unafraid of change, and excited by opportunities to better our services, our systems, and ourselves. Innovations and good ideas may be incremental or radical, and they can come from any corner of the organization at any time. #SeekImprovement<br></span><span><br><b>Be Excellent to Each Other.&nbsp;</b><br>We invest our time in quality work and giving customers and colleagues alike our respect, recognition, and support. #BeExcellent</span>','Deborah Kwon','2016-02-19 15:37:21.527373','2016-02-19 15:38:21.179650',13,'f');
